{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:psalms.107",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 107,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 107 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:1",
      "text": "O give thanks to the Lord, for he is good; for his steadfast love endures for ever!",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:2",
      "text": "Let the redeemed of the Lord say so, whom he has redeemed from trouble",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:3",
      "text": "and gathered in from the lands, from the east and from the west, from the north and from the south.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:4",
      "text": "Some wandered in desert wastes, finding no way to a city to dwell in;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:5",
      "text": "hungry and thirsty, their soul fainted within them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:6",
      "text": "Then they cried to the Lord in their trouble, and he delivered them from their distress;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:7",
      "text": "he led them by a straight way, till they reached a city to dwell in.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:8",
      "text": "Let them thank the Lord for his steadfast love, for his wonderful works to the sons of men!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:9",
      "text": "For he satisfies him who is thirsty, and the hungry he fills with good things.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:10",
      "text": "Some sat in darkness and in gloom, prisoners in affliction and in irons,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:11",
      "text": "for they had rebelled against the words of God, and spurned the counsel of the Most High.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:12",
      "text": "Their hearts were bowed down with hard labor; they fell down, with none to help.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:13",
      "text": "Then they cried to the Lord in their trouble, and he delivered them from their distress;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:14",
      "text": "he brought them out of darkness and gloom, and broke their bonds asunder.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:15",
      "text": "Let them thank the Lord for his steadfast love, for his wonderful works to the sons of men!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:16",
      "text": "For he shatters the doors of bronze, and cuts in two the bars of iron.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:17",
      "text": "Some were sick through their sinful ways, and because of their iniquities suffered affliction;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:18",
      "text": "they loathed any kind of food, and they drew near to the gates of death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:19",
      "text": "Then they cried to the Lord in their trouble, and he delivered them from their distress;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:20",
      "text": "he sent forth his word, and healed them, and delivered them from destruction.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:21",
      "text": "Let them thank the Lord for his steadfast love, for his wonderful works to the sons of men!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:22",
      "text": "And let them offer sacrifices of thanksgiving, and tell of his deeds in songs of joy!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:23",
      "text": "Some went down to the sea in ships, doing business on the great waters;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:24",
      "text": "they saw the deeds of the Lord, his wondrous works in the deep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:25",
      "text": "For he commanded, and raised the stormy wind, which lifted up the waves of the sea.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:26",
      "text": "They mounted up to heaven, they went down to the depths; their courage melted away in their evil plight;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:27",
      "text": "they reeled and staggered like drunken men, and were at their wits' end.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:28",
      "text": "Then they cried to the Lord in their trouble, and he delivered them from their distress;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:29",
      "text": "he made the storm be still, and the waves of the sea were hushed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:30",
      "text": "Then they were glad because they had quiet, and he brought them to their desired haven.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:31",
      "text": "Let them thank the Lord for his steadfast love, for his wonderful works to the sons of men!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:32",
      "text": "Let them extol him in the congregation of the people, and praise him in the assembly of the elders.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.33",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:33",
      "text": "He turns rivers into a desert, springs of water into thirsty ground,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.34",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:34",
      "text": "a fruitful land into a salty waste, because of the wickedness of its inhabitants.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.35",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:35",
      "text": "He turns a desert into pools of water, a parched land into springs of water.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.36",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:36",
      "text": "And there he lets the hungry dwell, and they establish a city to live in;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.37",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:37",
      "text": "they sow fields, and plant vineyards, and get a fruitful yield.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.38",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:38",
      "text": "By his blessing they multiply greatly; and he does not let their cattle decrease.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.39",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:39",
      "text": "When they are diminished and brought low through oppression, trouble, and sorrow,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.40",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:40",
      "text": "he pours contempt upon princes and makes them wander in trackless wastes;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.41",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:41",
      "text": "but he raises up the needy out of affliction, and makes their families like flocks.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.42",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:42",
      "text": "The upright see it and are glad; and all wickedness stops its mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.107.43",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 107,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 107:43",
      "text": "Whoever is wise, let him give heed to these things; let men consider the steadfast love of the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
